    • Method Detail

      • skipJsonifying

        public boolean skipJsonifying​(java.lang.String name)
        Determines whether a field should be omitted from being converted to JSON, based on info about it. To qualify based on the name is based on known patterns of variable names that are generated by AnyLogic.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the field
        Returns:
        true if it should *not* be included

      • skipJsonifying

        public boolean skipJsonifying​(java.lang.Class<?> clazz)
        Determines whether a field should be omitted from being converted to JSON, based on info about it. To qualify for being "inside" the package, the exact class must be inside the package. To qualify for being a class, the class must be assignable from the one in the filter (i.e., it can either be the same class as the one in the filter or a child class of it).
        Parameters:
        clazz -
        Returns:
        true if the provided class, or the package it's inside, is included in this object's filters

      • skipJsonifying

        public boolean skipJsonifying​(java.lang.String name,
                              java.lang.Class<?> clazz)
        Determines whether a field should be omitted from being converted to JSON, based on info about it. To qualify based on the name is based on known patterns of variable names that are generated by AnyLogic. To qualify for being "inside" the package, the exact class must be inside the package. To qualify for being a class, the class must be assignable from the one in the filter (i.e., it can either be the same class as the one in the filter or a child class of it).
        Parameters:
        name -
        clazz -
        Returns:
        true if the provided field should not be included in the outputted JSON

      • isGeneratedIncluded

        public boolean isGeneratedIncluded()

        Returns:

      • setGeneratedInclusion

        public JsonFilter setGeneratedInclusion​(boolean include)
        Various objects are auto-generated and added to your model by AnyLogic in response to certain user-defined objects/properties. For example, adding a Plot object with 3 lines set to the 'Value' type (i.e., not referencing a defined dataset) will autogenerate 3 DataSets with the name structure `_X_expressionN_dataSet_xjal`, where 'X' is the name of the plot and N is a number between 0 and 2 (for each of the 3 lines). This method lets you set whether you want to include those objects in the conversion to JSON. Setting this to false will do its best to ensure only user-added objects are in the outputted JSON. Specifically, it will exclude any objects suffixed with "_xjal".
        Parameters:
        include - Whether to include generated objects in the JSON conversion.
        Returns:
        a reference to this object
